local Tool = script.Parent local gui = Tool.ContestGui local playerGui = nil local opponentGui = nil local player = nil local opp = nil local opponentChangedSignal = nil local opponentDiedSignal = nil local gameCycles = 900 local gameTime = gameCycles local playerClicks = 0 local opponentClicks = 0 local playerPlaying = false local playerClickConnection = nil local opponentClickConnection = nil
Tool.Opponent.Value = nil local numbers = {Tool.One,Tool.Two,Tool.Three,Tool.Four,Tool.Five}
function onEquipped()
playerGui = gui:clone() player = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(Tool.Parent) playerGui.Parent = player.PlayerGui
opponentChangedSignal = Tool.Opponent.Changed:connect(opponentChanged)
for i = 1, #numbers do numbers[i]:Stop() end Tool.Start:Stop()
end
function onUnequipped()
playerGui:remove() playerGui = nil if opponentGui ~= nil and playerPlaying then opponentGui.AcceptFrame.Visible = false opponentGui.MainFrame.Visible = false opponentGui.StarterFrame.Visible = false opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.Visible = false opponentGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true opponentGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = player.Name .. " dropped out of the contest, you win!!!" opponentGui.PopupFrame.Accept.MouseButton1Down:connect(function() opponentGui:remove() opponentGui = nil opp = nil end) elseif opponentGui ~= nil then opponentGui:remove() opponentGui = nil opp = nil end
playerPlaying = false
Tool.Opponent.Value = nil opponentChangedSignal:disconnect()
for i = 1, #numbers do numbers[i]:Stop() end Tool.Start:Stop()
end
Tool.Equipped:connect(onEquipped) Tool.Unequipped:connect(onUnequipped)
local changing = false
function opponentChanged()
local value = Tool.Opponent.Value print("clickin'")
if value == nil or playerPlaying then return end local num = math.random(1,100) print("Called " .. tostring(num))
if changing then Tool.Opponent.Value = nil return end
print(value.Name .. tostring(num))
changing = true
opp = value
-- opponent is currently in another game, let the player know and reset if opp.PlayerGui:FindFirstChild("BattleshipGui") or opp.PlayerGui:FindFirstChild("ContestGui") then
playerGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = opp.Name .. " is currently playing another game!" playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true playerGui.PopupFrame.Accept.MouseButton1Down:connect(function() playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = false playerGui.StarterFrame.TXT.Text = "Click on a Robloxian to challenge them to a hot dog eating contest!" end)
else
if opponentGui == nil then opponentGui = gui:clone() end opponentGui.StarterFrame.Visible = false opponentGui.AcceptFrame.Visible = true opponentGui.AcceptFrame.TXT.Text = player.Name .. " challenges you to a hot dog eating contest!" opponentGui.Parent = opp.PlayerGui
playerGui.StarterFrame.TXT.Text = "Awaiting response from " .. opp.Name .. "..."
opponentGui.AcceptFrame.Accept.MouseButton1Down:connect(opponentAccepted) opponentGui.AcceptFrame.Decline.MouseButton1Down:connect(opponentDeclined) end
Tool.Opponent.Value = nil
wait(0.1) changing = false
end
function opponentDied()
playerPlaying = false
playerGui:remove() playerGui = Tool.ContestGui:clone() playerGui.Parent = player.PlayerGui
opponentGui:remove() opponentGui = nil opponentDiedSignal:disconnect()
end
function opponentAccepted()
opponentDiedSignal = opp.Character.Humanoid.Died:connect(opponentDied) playerPlaying = true
playerGui.StarterFrame.Visible = false opponentGui.AcceptFrame.Visible = false
-- let players know the game is about to start giveWarning()
-- set up for game and go! playerClicks = 0 opponentClicks = 0 gameTime = gameCycles
playerGui.MainFrame.Visible = true opponentGui.MainFrame.Visible = true
gameLoop()
-- let the players check out the game screen for a second before results wait(1)
playerGui.MainFrame.Visible = false opponentGui.MainFrame.Visible = false
resultsAndReset()
end
function gameLoop()
if playerClickConnection ~= nil then playerClickConnection:disconnect() end if opponentClickConnection ~= nil then opponentClickConnection:disconnect() end
-- allow players to start clicking playerClickConnection = playerGui.MainFrame.PlayerIcon.MouseButton1Down:connect(function() playerClicks = playerClicks + 1 end) opponentClickConnection = opponentGui.MainFrame.PlayerIcon.MouseButton1Down:connect(function() opponentClicks = opponentClicks + 1 end)
-- get to clicking! while gameTime > 0 do updateHotDogs() updateGameTime() end
end
function resultsAndReset()
playerClickConnection:disconnect() opponentClickConnection:disconnect()
-- player wins if playerClicks > opponentClicks then
playerGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = "Congratulations! You beat " .. opp.Name .. " by " .. tostring(playerClicks - opponentClicks) .. " hot dogs!" opponentGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = "Sorry, but " .. player.Name .. " ate " .. tostring(playerClicks - opponentClicks) .. " more hot dogs than you :(" playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true opponentGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true
-- opponent wins elseif playerClicks < opponentClicks then
opponentGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = "Congratulations! You beat " .. player.Name .. " by " .. tostring(opponentClicks - playerClicks) .. " hot dogs!" playerGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = "Sorry, but " .. opp.Name .. " ate " .. tostring(opponentClicks - playerClicks) .. " more hot dogs than you :(" playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true opponentGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true
-- a tie else
opponentGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = "Unbelievable! A tie! What a great match!" playerGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = "Unbelievable! A tie! What a great match!" playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true opponentGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true
end
playerGui.PopupFrame.Accept.MouseButton1Down:connect(function()
playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = false
playerGui.StarterFrame.TXT.Text = "Click on a Robloxian to challenge them to a hot dog eating contest!" playerGui.StarterFrame.Visible = true
playerPlaying = false
end)
opponentGui.PopupFrame.Accept.MouseButton1Down:connect(function()
opponentGui:remove() opponentGui = nil
end)
end
function giveWarning()
for i = 5, 1, -1 do if i == 5 then playerGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29384422" playerGui.WarmUpFrame.Visible = true
opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29384422" opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.Visible = true elseif i == 4 then opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29385594" playerGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29385594" elseif i == 3 then opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29386492" playerGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29386492" elseif i == 2 then opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29385652" playerGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29385652" elseif i == 1 then opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29385679" playerGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Image = "http://www.roblox.com/asset/?id=29385679" end numbers[i]:Play() scaleNumbers() end
opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.Visible = false playerGui.WarmUpFrame.Visible = false
Tool.Start:Play()
end
-- for sweet scaling effect win! function scaleNumbers()
local scaler = nil for i = 1, 70 do scaler = 2.5 * (i/70) playerGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Size = UDim2.new(0,32 * scaler,0,32 * scaler) opponentGui.WarmUpFrame.InstructionLabel.NumberLabel.Size = UDim2.new(0,32 * scaler,0,32 * scaler) wait() end
end
function updateHotDogs()
local playerPercentage = playerClicks/(playerClicks+opponentClicks) local opponentPercentage = opponentClicks/(playerClicks+opponentClicks)
-- update player gui playerGui.MainFrame.PlayerEaten.EatenNumber.Text = tostring(playerClicks) playerGui.MainFrame.OppEaten.EatenNumber.Text = tostring(opponentClicks) playerGui.MainFrame.PlayerBar.bar.Size = UDim2.new(0,64,0,-256 * playerPercentage) playerGui.MainFrame.OppBar.bar.Size = UDim2.new(0,64,0,-256 * opponentPercentage)
--update opponent gui opponentGui.MainFrame.PlayerEaten.EatenNumber.Text = tostring(opponentClicks) opponentGui.MainFrame.OppEaten.EatenNumber.Text = tostring(playerClicks) opponentGui.MainFrame.PlayerBar.bar.Size = UDim2.new(0,64,0,-256 * opponentPercentage) opponentGui.MainFrame.OppBar.bar.Size = UDim2.new(0,64,0,-256 * playerPercentage)
end
function updateGameTime()
wait(0.0333) gameTime = gameTime - 1 local size = (gameTime/gameCycles) * 150
playerGui.MainFrame.TimeTitle.EatenNumber.Size = UDim2.new(0,size,0,20) playerGui.MainFrame.TimeTitle.EatenNumber.Position = UDim2.new(0,-20 + (150 - (size))/2,0,60) opponentGui.MainFrame.TimeTitle.EatenNumber.Size = playerGui.MainFrame.TimeTitle.EatenNumber.Size opponentGui.MainFrame.TimeTitle.EatenNumber.Position = playerGui.MainFrame.TimeTitle.EatenNumber.Position
end
function opponentDeclined()
opponentGui.Parent = nil opponentGui:remove() opponentGui = nil playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = true playerGui.PopupFrame.TXT.Text = opp.Name .. " decided you are too awesome and declined your challenge." playerGui.PopupFrame.Accept.MouseButton1Down:connect(function() playerGui.PopupFrame.Visible = false playerGui.StarterFrame.TXT.Text = "Click on a Robloxian to challenge them to a hot dog eating contest!" end)
end

local Tool = script.Parent; local con = nil
function onButton1Down(mouse)
script.Parent.Opponent.Value = nil
if mouse ~= nil and mouse.Target ~= nil and mouse.Target.Parent ~= nil then local humanoid = mouse.Target.Parent:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") if humanoid ~= nil then local player = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(humanoid.Parent) if player ~= nil then script.Parent.Opponent.Value = player end end end
end
function onEquippedLocal(mouse)
if mouse == nil then print("Mouse not found") return end
con = mouse.Button1Down:connect(function() onButton1Down(mouse) end)
end
function onUnequippedLocal()
con:disconnect()
end
Tool.Unequipped:connect(onUnequippedLocal) Tool.Equipped:connect(onEquippedLocal)
